    <h1>Frozen thrills</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201121/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-21"><time>2020-11-21</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>The toki­doki Snow Hol­i­day at Ter­mi­nal 3 De­par­ture Hall is the largest dou­ble-storey snow fun house in Sin­ga­pore.</p>
    <p>As tem­per­a­tures in­side the fa­cil­ity can drop to more than mi­nus 10 deg C, spe­cial win­ter wear – from padded shoes to in­su­lat­ing jack­ets – is pro­vided for visi­tors be­fore they step in.</p>
    <p>Ex­pect near-bliz­zard con­di­tions with foam snow blasted at visi­tors, a light and sound show, lots of snow to build a snow­man with and a slide for chil­dren made from packed snow.</p>
    <p>Each ses­sion com­prises a safety brief­ing and prepa­ra­tion of about 20 min­utes and about 20 min­utes of play time.</p>
    <p>Info: Avail­able till Jan 3. Re­deem one com­pli­men­tary ac­tiv­ity pass for ev­ery $30 ($80 for su­per­mar­kets) spent at pub­lic ar­eas at Ter­mi­nals 1 and 3. A max­i­mum of four ac­tiv­ity passes in a sin­gle re­ceipt is al­lowed.</p>

